And now the Arsenal manager will see his midfielder to get to the bottom of what happened in America — but insisted he is not ‘deeply concerned’ by his actions.

Wenger said: ‘I haven’t spoken to him so it’s very difficult for me to make any statement. I know what you can make of the pictures.

‘I have to speak to him before I come out publicly. We will speak this week. I am not deeply concerned by it but I just want to know what happened.’

