Wenger did admit that next season could be make-or-break for Wilshere, saying: ‘He is at an age where you want him to move forward. He has potential. I believe, for him, what is most important is to have a good preparation and focus on getting really fit.

'Jack is a great player, has a football brain and is ambitious. I’m sure if he can stay injury-free he can have a great season.’

